Parliament is a hive of activity as those elected to serve in the National Assembly registered ahead of Wednesday morning's swearing-in ceremony. PARLIAMENT - South Africa's newly-elected Members of Parliament will be sworn in on Wednesday. The president of the country and the National Assembly Speaker and Deputy will also be elected. READ: Mbete, Gigaba withdraw from ANC MP list Members will be sworn in by Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng. They will either swear an oath before God or make a solemn affirmation. The incoming members had to go through orientation to find their feet. READ: Malema registers in Parliament ahead of swearing-in of MPs Parliament was a hive of activity on Tuesday as those elected registered ahead of the swearing-in ceremony. Wednesday will see the first sittings of both two Houses, establishing the sixth democratic Parliament.